{"title":"2022 Trek Rail eMTB debuts RockShox AirWiz Suspension Sensors, goes longer and further","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/28/2022-trek-rail-emtb-debuts-rockshox-airwiz-suspension-sensors-goes-longer-and-further/","date":1635433239000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081425/2022-trek-rail-emtb-hero-shot.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081425/2022-trek-rail-emtb-hero-shot-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"2022 trek rail 150mm travel emtb geometry adjust 29&quot; or mullet\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081425/2022-trek-rail-emtb-hero-shot-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081425/2022-trek-rail-emtb-hero-shot-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081425/2022-trek-rail-emtb-hero-shot-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081425/2022-trek-rail-emtb-hero-shot-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081425/2022-trek-rail-emtb-hero-shot-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081425/2022-trek-rail-emtb-hero-shot.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-276426\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Trek has overhauled their long-travel eMTB, updating the 2022 Trek Rail with a Slash-like geometry, mullet-ability, a bigger battery and improved Bosch Smart System integration. On top of that, the bike debuts AirWiz Suspension, the latest addition to RockShox’s electronic arsenal.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082829/2022-trek-rail-emtb-rockshox-airwiz-zeb-ultimate-fork.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082829/2022-trek-rail-emtb-rockshox-airwiz-zeb-ultimate-fork.jpg\" alt=\"2022 trek rail emtb airwiz suspension sensors\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082829/2022-trek-rail-emtb-rockshox-airwiz-zeb-ultimate-fork.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082829/2022-trek-rail-emtb-rockshox-airwiz-zeb-ultimate-fork-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082829/2022-trek-rail-emtb-rockshox-airwiz-zeb-ultimate-fork-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082829/2022-trek-rail-emtb-rockshox-airwiz-zeb-ultimate-fork-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082829/2022-trek-rail-emtb-rockshox-airwiz-zeb-ultimate-fork-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082829/2022-trek-rail-emtb-rockshox-airwiz-zeb-ultimate-fork-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The 9.9 and 9.8 models of the 2022 Trek Rail are the only ones to receive these major updates to the frame, battery and motor, with the RockShox AirWiz suspension reserved only for the top-end 9.9; the Rail 9.7, 9.5, 7 and 5 models will carry forward the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/09/12/trek-rail-powerfly-e-mtb-line-charge-up-blast-off-w-new-bosch-motors-batteries/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">frame from 2021</a>, with minor updates to componentry and colorways. Here’s everything you need to know about the 2022 Trek Rail 9.9 and 9.8.</p><h2>2022 Trek Rail 9.9 and 9.8 Models</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083723/2022-trek-rail-emtb-portrait.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083723/2022-trek-rail-emtb-portrait.jpg\" alt=\"2022 trek rail emtb 150mm travel\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083723/2022-trek-rail-emtb-portrait.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083723/2022-trek-rail-emtb-portrait-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083723/2022-trek-rail-emtb-portrait-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083723/2022-trek-rail-emtb-portrait-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083723/2022-trek-rail-emtb-portrait-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083723/2022-trek-rail-emtb-portrait-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The 2022 Trek Rail is now, essentially, an eMTB version of their enduro race bike, the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/09/03/2021-trek-slash-gets-more-travel-custom-thru-shaft-shock-knock-block-2-0-hidden-storage/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Trek Slash</a>. A 160mm travel fork paired with a 150mm travel rear end makes it 10mm shorter in travel than the Slash, but the geometry overhaul stretches the Rail out to deliver much longer reach across the board, surpassing the figures boasted by the Slash even.</p><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td>S</td><td>M</td><td>L</td><td>XL</td></tr><tr><td>2022 Trek Rail Reach (mm)</td><td>436</td><td>456</td><td>491</td><td>521</td></tr><tr><td>2021 Trek Rail Reach (mm)</td><td>420</td><td>445</td><td>465</td><td>495</td></tr><tr><td>2022 Trek Slash Reach (mm)</td><td>425</td><td>450</td><td>486</td><td>516</td></tr></tbody></table><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083719/2022-trek-rail-emtb-750wh-powertube-battery.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083719/2022-trek-rail-emtb-750wh-powertube-battery.jpg\" alt=\"2022 trek rail 750wh battery\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083719/2022-trek-rail-emtb-750wh-powertube-battery.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083719/2022-trek-rail-emtb-750wh-powertube-battery-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083719/2022-trek-rail-emtb-750wh-powertube-battery-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083719/2022-trek-rail-emtb-750wh-powertube-battery-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083719/2022-trek-rail-emtb-750wh-powertube-battery-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083719/2022-trek-rail-emtb-750wh-powertube-battery-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>Many of the changes were made to accommodate the new 750Wh PowerTube battery that replaces the 625Wh battery seen on the 2021 models; a 20% Wh increase for improved range. The exception here is the small frame; it is too small for the larger battery so holds onto the 625Wh. On the 9.8 model, the small frame’s dimensions also render it incompatible with most water bottles, with the exception of the <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=ale&amp;pw=147535&amp;mi=15585&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.trekbikes.com%2Finternational%2Fen_IN_TL%2Fequipment%2Fbike-accessories%2Fbike-water-bottles-cages%2Fbike-water-bottles%2Ftrek-voda-15-trails-water-bottle%2Fp%2F37385%2F\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"ugc\">Bontrager Voda 15</a> 444ml bottle. The small 9.9 won’t take a water bottle at all due to the clearance issues arising from the AirWiz module on the RockShox Super Deluxe Reactiv Thru-Shaft shock.</p><p>The 2022 frame retains the Mino Link, Trek-speak for a flip-chip located at the rocker-seat stay interface. This gives the bike two possible geometry configurations as a complete 29er, and it also allows the rear wheel to be swapped out for a 27.5″ wheel without messing with the bike’s geometry <em>too</em> much.</p><h3>Rail Stock 29″ Configuration</h3><div id=\"attachment_276573\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083319/2022-trek-rail-emtb-150mm-travel-29er-or-mullet.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276573\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083319/2022-trek-rail-emtb-150mm-travel-29er-or-mullet.jpg\" alt=\"2022 trek rail emtb longer geometry 150mm travel enduro emtb\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083319/2022-trek-rail-emtb-150mm-travel-29er-or-mullet.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083319/2022-trek-rail-emtb-150mm-travel-29er-or-mullet-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083319/2022-trek-rail-emtb-150mm-travel-29er-or-mullet-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083319/2022-trek-rail-emtb-150mm-travel-29er-or-mullet-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083319/2022-trek-rail-emtb-150mm-travel-29er-or-mullet-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28083319/2022-trek-rail-emtb-150mm-travel-29er-or-mullet-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276573\">Flipping the Mino Link to the high position will of course steepen that head tube angle and raise the BB height.</p></div><p>All Rail 9.8 and 9.9 frames will ship in the complete 29er config, with the Mino Link set to the Low position. That gives the bike a 64.6° head angle, just 0.3° slacker than the HA of the 2021 bike; barely worth a mention, really. More notable is the 77.1° effective seat tube angle, 2.1° steeper, seating the rider’s hips in a more powerful position over the bottom bracket for a more efficient pedal stroke.</p><h4>2022 Trek Rail 9.9 and 9.8 Geometry Chart in Low (Stock Position)</h4><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td>S</td><td>M</td><td>L</td><td>XL</td></tr><tr><td>Reach</td><td>436.3</td><td>456.3</td><td>491.3</td><td>521.2</td></tr><tr><td>Stack</td><td>624.8</td><td>629.3</td><td>642.8</td><td>656.3</td></tr><tr><td>Effective Top Tube Length</td><td>579.2</td><td>600.2</td><td>638.3</td><td>671.5</td></tr><tr><td>Chainstay Length</td><td>446.7</td><td>446.7</td><td>446.7</td><td>446.7</td></tr><tr><td>Headtube Angle</td><td>64.6</td><td>64.6</td><td>64.6</td><td>64.6</td></tr><tr><td>Headtube Length</td><td>105</td><td>110</td><td>125</td><td>140</td></tr><tr><td>Effective Seat Tube Angle</td><td>77.1</td><td>77.1</td><td>77.1</td><td>77.1</td></tr><tr><td>BB Drop</td><td>27.1</td><td>27.1</td><td>27.1</td><td>27.0</td></tr><tr><td>BB Height</td><td>346.4</td><td>346.4</td><td>346.4</td><td>346.5</td></tr><tr><td>Standover</td><td>760.7</td><td>772.7</td><td>769.7</td><td>767.8</td></tr><tr><td>Wheelbase</td><td>1213.4</td><td>1235.5</td><td>1277.0</td><td>1313.4</td></tr><tr><td>Front Centre</td><td>768.0</td><td>790.1</td><td>831.5</td><td>868.0</td></tr><tr><td>Fork A2C</td><td>576</td><td>576</td><td>576</td><td>576</td></tr><tr><td>Fork Offset</td><td>43</td><td>43</td><td>43</td><td>43</td></tr><tr><td>Trail</td><td>129.6</td><td>129.6</td><td>129.7</td><td>129.7</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Rail Mullet Configuration</h3><p>The stock 29er won’t be for everyone, especially if you find yourself getting buzzed by the back tire on steep descents, or you feel the need for snappier cornering.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081428/2022-trek-rail-emtb-mino-link-mullet.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081428/2022-trek-rail-emtb-mino-link-mullet.jpg\" alt=\"2022 trek rail mino link flip chip geometry adjust accomodate 27.5&quot; rear wheel mullet configuration\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081428/2022-trek-rail-emtb-mino-link-mullet.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081428/2022-trek-rail-emtb-mino-link-mullet-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081428/2022-trek-rail-emtb-mino-link-mullet-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081428/2022-trek-rail-emtb-mino-link-mullet-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081428/2022-trek-rail-emtb-mino-link-mullet-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081428/2022-trek-rail-emtb-mino-link-mullet-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>If you do plan to mullet your 2022 Trek Rail, the brand strongly recommend you also switch the Mino Link to the high position. Why? To make up for the lower rear axle position, specifically the lower BB height and slacker angles that come with it. The switch to a 27.5″ rear wheel does still impact upon these measurements, however; you’ll end up with a 63.9° head angle, 76.4° seat tube angle, and a 336mm BB height, 10mm lower than the stock 29er.</p><h4>2022 Trek Rail 9.9 and 9.8 Geometry Chart Mullet Configuration (High Position)</h4><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td>S</td><td>M</td><td>L</td><td>XL</td></tr><tr><td>Reach</td><td>428.0</td><td>448.1</td><td>483.2</td><td>513.2</td></tr><tr><td>Stack</td><td>630.5</td><td>635.2</td><td>648.9</td><td>662.6</td></tr><tr><td>Effective Top Tube Length</td><td>581.0</td><td>602.1</td><td>640.2</td><td>673.4</td></tr><tr><td>Chainstay Length</td><td>446.7</td><td>446.7</td><td>446.7</td><td>446.7</td></tr><tr><td>Headtube Angle</td><td>63.9</td><td>63.9</td><td>63.9</td><td>63.9</td></tr><tr><td>Headtube Length</td><td>105</td><td>110</td><td>125</td><td>140</td></tr><tr><td>Effective Seat Tube Angle</td><td>76.4</td><td>76.4</td><td>76.4</td><td>76.4</td></tr><tr><td>BB Drop</td><td>27.1</td><td>27.1</td><td>27.1</td><td>27.0</td></tr><tr><td>BB Height</td><td>336.3</td><td>336.2</td><td>336.0</td><td>335.9</td></tr><tr><td>Standover</td><td>751.9</td><td>763.8</td><td>760.6</td><td>758.4</td></tr><tr><td>Wheelbase</td><td>1213.4</td><td>1235.5</td><td>1277.0</td><td>1313.4</td></tr><tr><td>Front Centre</td><td>768.0</td><td>790.1</td><td>831.5</td><td>868.0</td></tr><tr><td>Fork A2C</td><td>576</td><td>576</td><td>576</td><td>576</td></tr><tr><td>Fork Offset</td><td>43</td><td>43</td><td>43</td><td>43</td></tr><tr><td>Trail</td><td>135.4</td><td>135.3</td><td>135.1</td><td>135.0</td></tr></tbody></table><p>In conjunction with these geometry updates, Trek have tweaked the OCLV (Optimum Compaction Low Void) Carbon frame to accommodate that massive 750Wh battery, also increasing the seat tube diameter to 34.9mm and enlarging the headtube to 1.8″ to enhance stiffness. Steering angle is also massively increased from 58° to 72° thanks to <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/09/03/2021-trek-slash-gets-more-travel-custom-thru-shaft-shock-knock-block-2-0-hidden-storage/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Knock Block 2.0</a>. It is compatible with the infinite-radius chip but Trek recommend you do continue to run the Knock Block chip to protect the KIOX display. Which brings us to…</p><h3>Bosch Smart System</h3><div id=\"attachment_276564\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081418/2022-trek-rail-bosch-performance-line-cx-motor.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276564\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081418/2022-trek-rail-bosch-performance-line-cx-motor.jpg\" alt=\"2022 trek rail bosch performance line cx motor\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081418/2022-trek-rail-bosch-performance-line-cx-motor.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081418/2022-trek-rail-bosch-performance-line-cx-motor-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081418/2022-trek-rail-bosch-performance-line-cx-motor-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081418/2022-trek-rail-bosch-performance-line-cx-motor-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081418/2022-trek-rail-bosch-performance-line-cx-motor-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081418/2022-trek-rail-bosch-performance-line-cx-motor-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276564\">The Bosch Performance Line CX motor is powered by a 750Wh PowerTube on the M, L and XL frames; the small only fits the 625 Wh battery</p></div><p>Trek boast the new Rail sees better-than-ever integration of the BOSCH Performance Line CX motor, with the bike, KIOX display and the Flow App on your Smart Phone.&nbsp;</p><div id=\"attachment_276565\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081422/2022-trek-rail-bosch-smart-system-led-remote.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276565\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081422/2022-trek-rail-bosch-smart-system-led-remote.jpg\" alt=\"2022 trek rail bosch smart system led remote\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081422/2022-trek-rail-bosch-smart-system-led-remote.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081422/2022-trek-rail-bosch-smart-system-led-remote-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081422/2022-trek-rail-bosch-smart-system-led-remote-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081422/2022-trek-rail-bosch-smart-system-led-remote-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081422/2022-trek-rail-bosch-smart-system-led-remote-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081422/2022-trek-rail-bosch-smart-system-led-remote-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276565\">Activate walk-mode using the Bosch Smart System LED Remote when you need a bit of assistance to push the bike to the top</p></div><p>A highlight of the new system is the new LED Remote. This is responsible for connecting the Rail eMTB, via Bluetooth, to the Flow App on your Smart Phone. That allows you to see a host of information about your ride, more than the KIOX display is able to show you, on the go. The Flow App works with 3rd party software too, so you can upload your data to Apple Health; Bosch are currently working on integration with Strava, Komoot and other popular platforms.</p><p>Via the Flow App, you can view and adjust the maximum speed, maximum torque, dynamics and support for each pedal-assist mode. As the software improves, you can receive updates “over-the-air” via the Flow App, so that your eMTB is always up to date.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081414/2022-trek-rail-bosch-kiox-300-knock-block-mounted-display.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081414/2022-trek-rail-bosch-kiox-300-knock-block-mounted-display.jpg\" alt=\"bosch smart system kiox 300 display mounted to knock block of 2022 trek rail emtb\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081414/2022-trek-rail-bosch-kiox-300-knock-block-mounted-display.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081414/2022-trek-rail-bosch-kiox-300-knock-block-mounted-display-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081414/2022-trek-rail-bosch-kiox-300-knock-block-mounted-display-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081414/2022-trek-rail-bosch-kiox-300-knock-block-mounted-display-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081414/2022-trek-rail-bosch-kiox-300-knock-block-mounted-display-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081414/2022-trek-rail-bosch-kiox-300-knock-block-mounted-display-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The LED Remote has five LEDs that let you know the charge status of your battery. These are color coded, so they also tell you what mode of power-assist you’re using. The updated KIOX 300 display now lacks buttons entirely; that’s because it is the LED Remote that switches between the different displays. This has made the system a little safer, as you now don’t need to take your hand away from the handlebar to flick through the different screens when looking for the ride info you want.&nbsp;</p><h3>RockShox AirWiz Suspension and TyreWiz 2.0</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081436/2022-trek-rail-rockshox-zeb-ultimate-airwiz.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081436/2022-trek-rail-rockshox-zeb-ultimate-airwiz.jpg\" alt=\"rockshox zeb ultimate airwiz sensor 2022 trek rail emtb\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081436/2022-trek-rail-rockshox-zeb-ultimate-airwiz.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081436/2022-trek-rail-rockshox-zeb-ultimate-airwiz-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081436/2022-trek-rail-rockshox-zeb-ultimate-airwiz-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081436/2022-trek-rail-rockshox-zeb-ultimate-airwiz-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081436/2022-trek-rail-rockshox-zeb-ultimate-airwiz-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081436/2022-trek-rail-rockshox-zeb-ultimate-airwiz-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The 2022 Trek Rail 9.9 model is the first bike to benefit from RockShox AirWiz, a product that is exclusive to Trek. The ZEB Ultimate fork and Super Deluxe Reactiv Thur-Shaft shock both get an AirWiz module. Using a traffic light system, the AirWiz is designed to give the rider immediate feedback as to the air pressure of their suspension; like an automatic pre-ride check.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082516/2022-trek-rail-9-airwiz-rockshox-super-deluxe-reactiv-thrushaft-shock.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082516/2022-trek-rail-9-airwiz-rockshox-super-deluxe-reactiv-thrushaft-shock.jpg\" alt=\"2022 trek rail emtb airwiz reactiv thrushaft shock rockshox\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082516/2022-trek-rail-9-airwiz-rockshox-super-deluxe-reactiv-thrushaft-shock.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082516/2022-trek-rail-9-airwiz-rockshox-super-deluxe-reactiv-thrushaft-shock-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082516/2022-trek-rail-9-airwiz-rockshox-super-deluxe-reactiv-thrushaft-shock-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082516/2022-trek-rail-9-airwiz-rockshox-super-deluxe-reactiv-thrushaft-shock-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082516/2022-trek-rail-9-airwiz-rockshox-super-deluxe-reactiv-thrushaft-shock-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28082516/2022-trek-rail-9-airwiz-rockshox-super-deluxe-reactiv-thrushaft-shock-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>From the SRAM AXS App on your Smart Phone, you can tell the AirWiz your desired air pressure range. If the fork or shock pressure sits outwith that pre-set range, the light will be red, indicating a top up is required. If the light is green, then you’re good to go.</p><p>This is <em>not</em> an integrated <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2018/02/15/shockwiz-works-more-magic-with-custom-tuning-trail-profiling-lower-pricing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ShockWiz</a>. Given SRAM’s ownership of the suspension setup device, however, we do wonder whether AirWiz will evolve into that. It certainly seems possible, given the capabilities of <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/02/09/mondraker-mind-integrated-telemetry-tool-perfects-easy-intuitive-suspension-setup/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Mondraker’s MIND telemetry</a>, though that uses magnetic field sensors, as opposed to air pressure, to measure travel usage.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081432/2022-trek-rail-emtb-tirewiz-2-bontrager-wheel-compatible.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081432/2022-trek-rail-emtb-tirewiz-2-bontrager-wheel-compatible.jpg\" alt=\"tyrewiz 2.0 on bontrager line pro wheels 2022 trek rail 9.9 emtb\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081432/2022-trek-rail-emtb-tirewiz-2-bontrager-wheel-compatible.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081432/2022-trek-rail-emtb-tirewiz-2-bontrager-wheel-compatible-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081432/2022-trek-rail-emtb-tirewiz-2-bontrager-wheel-compatible-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081432/2022-trek-rail-emtb-tirewiz-2-bontrager-wheel-compatible-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081432/2022-trek-rail-emtb-tirewiz-2-bontrager-wheel-compatible-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28081432/2022-trek-rail-emtb-tirewiz-2-bontrager-wheel-compatible-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The 2022 Trek Rail also sees the debut of the TyreWiz 2.0, exclusive to Bontrager wheels. Like the AirWiz, TyreWiz 2.0 also makes use of a traffic light system. Pre-set your desired tire pressures in the SRAM AXS App and you’re ready to go. Again, green indicates your pressures are correct, while red indicates the need for a top up. The base of the device is shaped complementary to the rim of the Bontrager Line Pro 30 wheelset it sits on.</p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><div id=\"attachment_276585\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090747/2022-trek-rail-98-gx-axs.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276585\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090747/2022-trek-rail-98-gx-axs.jpg\" alt=\"2022 trek rail 9.8 gx axs\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090747/2022-trek-rail-98-gx-axs.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090747/2022-trek-rail-98-gx-axs-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090747/2022-trek-rail-98-gx-axs-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090747/2022-trek-rail-98-gx-axs-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090747/2022-trek-rail-98-gx-axs-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090747/2022-trek-rail-98-gx-axs-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276585\">The 2022 Trek Rail 9.8 GX AXS</p></div><p>There are three models of the 2022 Trek Rail 9.8 featuring the Bosch Smart System; the GX, XT and GX AXS. The GX and XT have a suggested retail pricing of $8,999.99 USD, while the GX AXS model with electronic gearing and Reverb AXS dropper post is priced at $9,999.99 USD.</p><div id=\"attachment_276586\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090750/2022-trek-rail-emtb-99-xx1-axs.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276586\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090750/2022-trek-rail-emtb-99-xx1-axs.jpg\" alt=\"2022 trek rail 9.9 xx1 axs\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1066\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090750/2022-trek-rail-emtb-99-xx1-axs.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090750/2022-trek-rail-emtb-99-xx1-axs-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090750/2022-trek-rail-emtb-99-xx1-axs-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090750/2022-trek-rail-emtb-99-xx1-axs-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090750/2022-trek-rail-emtb-99-xx1-axs-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/28090750/2022-trek-rail-emtb-99-xx1-axs-1536x1023.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276586\">2022 Trek Rail 9.9 XX1 AXS</p></div><p>Only the 2022 Trek Rail 9.9 bikes get the RockShox AirWiz suspension; the 9.9 XTR retails at $12,499.99 USD while the XX1 AXS model will set you back an eye watering $13,499.99 USD.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=ale&amp;pw=147535&amp;mi=15585&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.trekbikes.com%2Fus%2Fen_US%3Fclear%3Dtrue\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"ugc\"><em>TrekBikes.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"64e7395cf08d44c6bdb223fb7746c3e227fa8d7e768e42eeae52bef33e11823f","category":"Cycling"}